02/02/2004
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The trial of one of the most senior Bosnian Serb wartime leaders is scheduled to begin in The Hague on Tuesday (3 February). 
Momcilo Krajisnik, the speaker of the Serb entity's parliament from 1992-1995, faces eight counts of genocide, crimes against humanity and war crimes.
In other news, Croatian President Stipe Mesic says he expects more indictments against Croats. 
"From what I know, two new indictments will arrive, but I do not know who will be indicted," Mesic told <I> Jutarnji List</I> in an interview Monday. 
(AFP, Jutarnji List, HINA - 02/02/04)
